## Go way of "toString"

Your type just need to adhere to the [Stringer interface](https://pkg.go.dev/fmt#Stringer)

```go
// example:
type Quotation struct {
	quote  string
	author string
}

func (q Quotation) String() string {
	return fmt.Sprintf("%s says, %q.", q.author, q.quote)
}
```

## reading lines from the user

```go
// NOTE: I learned that Scanln (by default) reads only the first word
// if the string has spaces.
var str string
fmt.Scanln(&str)

// NOTE: this method reads the whole line, but keeps the '\n' char.
reader := bufio.NewReader(os.Stdin)
str, _ := reader.ReadString('\n')

// NOTE: this is the one to be used! :)
scanner := bufio.NewScanner(os.Stdin)
scanner.Scan()
str := scanner.Text()
```

## if short statement

```go
func pow(x, n, lim float64) float64 {

  // v is only available inside the if and else blocks
  if v := math.Pow(x, n); v < lim {
    return v
  } else {
    fmt.Printf("%g >= %g\n", v, lim)
  }

  // can't use v here, though
  return lim
}
```
